&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking applications from individuals who can demonstrate practical experience and knowledge of both office cleaning and/or experience of working in a healthcare environment, although full training will be provided for the right candidate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a role working across hospital wards and administration buildings at Alderney Hospital. A clean driving licence and use of own car would be beneficial – (business mileage paid).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a part-time post, 30 hours per week, 6hrs per day, 5 days per week, will include some weekends, fixed term for 6 months.  (The salary is plus enhancements for weekend and bank holiday working, where applicable)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates will need to be physically fit due to the nature of the work and the post will be subject to a Standard DBS checks (formerly CRB).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A range of benefits exist including apprenticeship scheme, pension scheme, paid leave entitlements and staff discounts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Jane Cole&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Manager&lt;/p&gt;
